items.name: Foolkat_Kickass_Comic_Merge
items.description:
Update 7/13/23 - Some of you may have noticed that the permissions for this model have changed. The reason is because I noticed that one of the models in the mix requires the same permissions to be used for any merges using said model. Because of that, I've had to change the permissions to match.

This is a merge of three comic models I like to see what results I could get. I merged Comic Babes + mcbsMachinecodeComicsV2 + DuskfallsComicAnimePunk to get this interesting mix. It works especially well with fantasy style art and can create SFW and NSFW images.

No VAE required. I baked in Blessed2 VAE.

I merged the models together to get a style that doesn't require trigger words, but you should still be able to use the trigger words from each of the original models to tweak the images to your liking.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

Spratt's artistic versatility and dedication to his craft have garnered him a significant online following, with his artwork often shared and celebrated on social media platforms. items.name: Jules Bastien-Lepage Style
items.description:
Jules Bastien-Lepage was a French painter active during the late 19th century. He was a prominent figure in the Naturalist movement and is known for his realistic and emotionally evocative paintings.

Bastien-Lepage's artwork focused on depicting scenes of rural life and the everyday experiences of common people. He had a keen eye for capturing the nuances of light, color, and texture, which gave his paintings a sense of depth and realism.

One of his most famous works is "The Haymakers," which depicts two laborers taking a break from their work in a sun-drenched field. This painting exemplifies Bastien-Lepage's ability to convey a sense of atmosphere and mood, as well as his attention to the human figure and its relationship to the surrounding environment.

Bastien-Lepage's style combined elements of Realism and Impressionism. He aimed to depict subjects truthfully and accurately, but also incorporated loose brushwork and a sensitivity to capturing fleeting moments and natural lighting conditions.

His paintings often conveyed a sense of empathy and humanity, emphasizing the dignity and beauty in everyday life. Bastien-Lepage's ability to capture the essence of his subjects and evoke emotion made him highly regarded among his contemporaries.

Tragically, Bastien-Lepage's career was cut short when he passed away at the young age of 36. However, his influence on the art world continued to be felt, and his legacy as a skilled and empathetic painter lives on.

Jules Bastien-Lepage's realistic and emotionally evocative paintings contributed to the Naturalist movement and left a lasting impact on the art world. His ability to capture the essence of everyday life, infuse his works with a sense of atmosphere, and evoke genuine emotion make him a celebrated figure in the history of art.

Her artworks often featured children dressed in period clothing, set in idyllic outdoor scenes or domestic settings. One of her most notable works is "Under the Window," a collection of illustrations and verses that became immensely popular. The book showcased her talent for capturing the spirit of childhood in a gentle and whimsical manner.

Greenaway's illustrations had a significant impact on children's literature and influenced the development of children's book illustration. Her distinctive style, which combined elements of realism with a touch of fantasy, created an enduring aesthetic that continues to inspire artists and illustrators today.

In addition to her illustration work, Greenaway also wrote and published several books. Her writings often complemented her illustrations, further enhancing the storytelling experience for young readers.

Catherine Greenaway's contributions to children's literature and illustration left a lasting legacy. Her enchanting and nostalgic artworks continue to captivate generations of readers, and her influence can be seen in the works of many contemporary illustrators. She remains an important figure in the history of children's book illustration and is remembered for her timeless creations that have brought joy to countless children and adults alike.

Quick start guide

  • Some Loras are tested and they work well with the model

    • 512x1024 is especially good for full-body portraits.

    • Twitter advice: Twitter will crop 1:2 ratio images in a very unfortunate way, so 512x768 is a very good choice if you want to upload to Twitter

  • Loras that nicely complement this model:

    • add_detail: Adds much more detail to the renders. But be aware, this LoRA quickly starts to mess with hands (using Ardmix)

How to write prompts?

  • Check the preview images. A more detailed work-through will come soon.

  • Use '1boy' to target male characters. The required weight might vary from prompt to prompt. A weight between 1.0 to 1.3 is recommended.

    • An additional step might be to add '1girl' to your negative prompt. This isn't required but might help if the model acts very stubbornly.

Roadmap

  1. Increase the amount of male training data (Trigger words like 1boy, 2boys).

I trained it with just shapes, switched back to LyCoris and played around with the training settings to generate this version of the model.

Thx to rfktr for his helpful input on my water model. I applied what I learned in this model, too.

Works without triggerword, mostly.

Have fun breathing some air into your images. You can use it to "morph" things into windy shapes or use it as an art style.

Tried to show what it's capable of in the showcase.

If you like what I'm creating feel free to buy me a coffee. ;)

items.name: Judy-Zootopia

This is my first attempt to train a LoRA and I'm thrilled to share it to the community. This LoRA learns to depict Judy in the movie Zootopia. It is trained using kohya-ss's sd-scripts in the DreamBooth way.

Notes:

  • It's better to use Rev Animated as the base model because I trained the LoRA on it.

  • A weight of 0.9-1 should be fine.

  • The trigger word is "Judy bunny".

  • The clothes are not decomposed from the character so it likely produces Judy in the police uniform with a badge.

  • Some common problems are the wrong numbers of ears and multiple pupils in one eye. I'm glad to know if someone has ideas on how to solve these problems.

items.name: Mango Sticky Rice
items.description:
Mango Sticky Rice is meant to produce photorealistic images of various themes. I've tested with fantasy, scifi, landscapes, mechs, cybernetics, robots, women, men, etc. Sometimes the initial generation may look more like an illustration (particularly if the character or focus is far away), but using Loopback Scaler (my preferred method) or Highres fix will help pull it back to photorealism rather well.

One thing to note is that it can be difficult to generate a male character sometimes since so much training has a female bias. I highly recommend Zovya's Gender Slider to help with this.

Please note that the prompts shown for the images are the initial generation prompts. When using Loopback Scaler or upscaling, I modify the prompts to bring out or reduce certain features, and of course prompts become very simple for inpainting most of the time.

For final upscaling I use Ultimate SD Upscaler.

These are the two upscalers I use I this point:

4x-UltraMix Restore
UltraSharp

But others might like these as well:

Foolhardy Remacri
NMKD Siax 200k
NMKD Superscale SP 178000 G
lollypop

I almost exclusively use DPM++ 2M Karras for generation and upscaling through Ultimate SD Upscaler. I do swap to DDIM for Loopback Scaler though!

Be nice, have fun!

Steven Frederic Seagal (/s…™Àà…°…ëÀêl/; born April 10, 1952) is an American-born actor, screenwriter, and martial artist. A 7th-dan black belt in aikido, he began his adult life as a martial arts instructor in Japan[2] and eventually ended up running his father-in-law's dojo.[3] He later moved to Los Angeles where he had the same profession. In 1988, Seagal made his acting debut in Above the Law. By 1991, he had starred in four films. Seagal also holds Serbian and Russian citizenship.

In 1992, he played Navy SEAL counter-terrorist expert Casey Ryback in Under Siege. During the latter half of the 1990s, Seagal starred in three more feature films and the direct-to-video film The Patriot. Subsequently, his career shifted to mostly direct-to-video productions. He has since appeared in films and reality shows, including Steven Seagal: Lawman, which depicted Seagal performing duties as a reserve deputy sheriff.

Seagal is a guitarist and has released two studio albums, Songs from the Crystal Cave and Mojo Priest, and performed on the scores of several of his films. He has worked with Stevie Wonder and Tony Rebel, who both performed on his debut album. He has been involved in a line of "therapeutic oil" products and energy drinks. Seagal is an environmentalist,[4] animal rights activist, and supporter of 14th Dalai Lama Tenzin Gyatso.[5][6] He is a supporter of Vladimir Putin, to whom he once referred as "one of the great living world leaders".[7] He was granted both Russian[8] and Serbian citizenship in 2016. In 2018, he was appointed Russia's special envoy to the U.S.[9]

In the negative prompt add "(two tone lighting)" and "(dimly lit)". It's preferrable but it helps to get clean results.

Finally you can use "LowRa" with negative values to brighten the results a bit more. Hope you like it :)

Support me on buymeacoffee if you like my work.
